Risk Mitigation: Quantitative Risk Assessment
Indicators & Warnings (I&W) Analysis — Canada Life Acquisition of Santé Circle Health

---
This notebook supports the Risk Mitigation assignment by implementing:
1. **Monte Carlo Simulation** for R-003 (Cross-Selling Synergy Shortfall) and R-013 (Legacy System Incompatibility)
2. **Expected Monetary Value (EMV)** calculation for R-010 (PHI Data Breach)
3. **Random Forest Classification** for PHI breach risk prediction (R-010)
4. **Gradient Boosting Model** for system incompatibility risk prediction (R-013)
5. **Risk Register Update** with quantitative results

Risk R-003: Cross-Selling Revenue Synergy Shortfall
Qualitative Score: 20 (Likelihood 4 × Impact 5) — HIGH PRIORITY
Risk: Cross-selling revenue synergies fall short of projections
Risk Owner: Chief Revenue Officer

Monte Carlo Simulation Approach
We model projected Year 1 cross-sell revenue by varying three key input parameters across 10,000 simulation runs:

Broker Adoption Rate: % of Canada Life brokers actively promoting Santé Circle services
Client Uptake Rate: % of clients who convert per outreach campaign
Revenue per Converted Client: Annual CAD revenue per client acquired through cross-sell

Risk R-010: PHI Data Breach
Qualitative Score: 15 (Likelihood 3 × Impact 5) — HIGH PRIORITY
Risk: PHI data breach triggers regulatory action and public backlash
Risk Owner: CISO / Legal

Quantitative Assessment Approach
Two methods are applied:
Expected Monetary Value (EMV): Industry benchmark probability × financial impact
Random Forest Classification: Identifies the highest-risk system integration scenarios based on synthetic breach predictor data

Risk R-013: Legacy System Incompatibility
Qualitative Score: 16 (Likelihood 4 × Impact 4) — HIGH PRIORITY
Risk: Legacy system incompatibility disrupts data exchange
Risk Owner: CTO / IT PMO

Quantitative Assessment Approach
Monte Carlo Simulation: Models financial cost of system downtime during integration
Gradient Boosting Model: Identifies highest-risk integration scenarios from system compatibility features

